title: For Sale:  NIB Czech Vz.2008 Rifle VZ58 milled Free Shipping!
postcontent:
Factory new, unfired, Century Arms Czech Vz.2008 Sporter, chambered for the 7.62x39mm cartridge. The Vz.2008 Sporter is a semi-auto rebuild of the original Czech Vz.58 assault rifle, which has been in use for over half a century. This rifle has a milled receiver, last-round BHO, and metal side folding buttstock.

The Vz.58 has been the standard issue assault rifle of the Czech military since the late 1950s. It was designed primarly after the AK-47 but with a milled receiver and about a pound lighter. However, about all it has in common with the AK is its 7.62x39mm caliber. In all other ways, the Vz.58 is a unique weapon.

It features a milled receiver, lightweight barrel, short-stroke gas system (similar to that found in the FN FAL or SKS), tilting locked breech, and last-round bolt hold open device. Even though it has a milled receiver, the Vz is over a pound lighter than even a stamped receiver AKM. Its magazines are also made of a lightweight alloy; as weight was of prime concern to the developers. It is also shorter/more compact than the AK.

The Century Vz.2008 Sporter is built from original Czech mfg parts, using a newly made US milled receiver and 16" long threaded barrel. All other parts are original, including the furniture, bolt group, gas system, sights, dustcover, and more. It can feed from original surplus magazines and does feature the BHO. It has all of the military features including bayonet lug, threaded barrel with muzzle brake, and sling swivals. This particular rifle has an original Czech metal right side folding buttstock, which when folded, makes the weapon extremely compact.

$579.99 shipped to your ffl.

Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.

The USP is available in nine trigger/firing mode configurations and three calibers. 9mm, .40 S&W and .45 ACP.

Model: 	 H-223
Caliber: 	 5.56mm NATO
Barrel Length: 	 16 inch

OPERATING SYSTEM: Gas trap/piston operation, rotating bolt (short stroke system), reversible gas piston for suppressed or non-suppressed operation. Unlike some other "op-rod" systems, on the HOGAN gun, op-rod springs have been eliminated due to possible damage and system failure during sustained firing of the gun. The HOGAN gun system has been designed and manufactured to greatly decrease/eliminate heat, carbon build-up, gas leaks, fouling and wear/tear on operating parts which can have an adverse effect on an operating system. Each piece of operating system is hard chrome plated and/or melonite heat treated making them almost self lubricating and act as non stick surfaces making them easy to clean and maintain. Operates in semi-automatic, but can be made full-auto for Military and Law Enforcement. UPPER RECEIVER: Billet machined from 7075 aluminum forgings, (aircraft alumimun alloy), into an A3 flattop upper receiver to fit varied handrails or a 1-piece upper receiver to fit our Free Floating Monolithic rail system Electro-less *silicone Nickel on the interior (*depending on availability when rifle is shipped) Finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan, or clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green, (depending on customer preference or gun design). CHARGING HANDLE: Billet machined from 7075 aluminum bar stock, manufactured with an oversized grip and locking latch. Black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625, duo colored with electro less Nickel coating/black anodize to Mil-Spec 9625 or NP3™ coated, (depending on customer preference or firearm design). HEAT SINK BARREL NUT and WEDGEBLOCK: “Patented” oversized 3.375” heat sink barrel nut design billet machined from 6061 T-6 aluminum, heat treated and black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625 Provides strength, rigidity to rail system and works as a heat sink to greatly reduce heat buildup utilizing a larger surface area and cooling fins. Comes in sizes short, long or ribbed to meet specifications of firearm design. Wedgeblock comes in 2 styles flat for A3 flattop upper receiver or grooved for monolithic railed receiver, billet machined from 6061 T-6 aluminum extrusion, heat treated and black anodized to Mil-Spec 8625. HANDGUARDS/RAILS: Aircraft aluminum alloy precision machined from 6061 T-6 extrusion Free Floating Monolithic Tactical and Hunter hand guards or Monolithic top rail finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan, or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green. PISTON and OP ROD: Reversible gas piston for suppressed or non-suppressed operation billet machined from 4140 high temp steel round bar, heat treated to Mil-Spec, ground to size, hard chrome plated. Tool steel op-rod, heat treated to Mil-Spec from PCS Company. GAS BLOCK ASSEMBLY and GAS PLUG: Gas block: billet machined from 4140 aircraft quality steel bar stock, heat treated to Mil-Spec. Gas tube: 4130 aircraft quality tubing. Block and tube are joined then mated with barrel (matching serial#’s added), then melonite heat treated together. Gas plug: billet machined from 4140/4142 steel bar, heat treated to Mil-Spec, ground to size, mag phosphate on top, NP3 coated, and/or chrome plated with blackened top. BOLT and CARRIER: .223 bolt: machined from 9310 steel bar stock, phosphate heat treated to Mil-Spec .223 and mag particle inspected, hard chrome plated. Carrier: billet machined from single piece of 8620 steel - integral keyed steel bolt carrier (machined as one piece to leave key in place). Heat treated per Mil-Spec, Nickel Teflon plated. HOGAN SPECIFICATIONS: Smaller parts like springs, screws and washers are sourced from domestic manufacturers. Everything in a HOGAN gun is 100% made in the U.S.A. All raw materials are manufactured from U.S. steel mills. All heat treats, plating/coatings, are completed by U.S. owned and operated manufactures. All accessory and component parts on weapon systems are from U.S. owned and operated manufacturers. All HOGAN weapon systems are 100% pure American made. BARREL: Barrel blanks are supplied by Rock Creek Barrels, Inc. and completed to final specification at Hogan Guns. Medium contour, hand lapped button twisted rifled, 6 fluted to improve rigidity and heat dissipation, reduce weight, improve accuracy by reducing barrel vibration when firing. 4150 Mil-B-11595 chrome moly vanadium alloy (machine gun rated). 70 Rockwell case hardened heat treated “5R” polygonal barrels are 2 times harder than Mil-Spec and hammer forged barrels. Corrosion resistant and 10 times thicker and harder than Mil-Spec chromed lining. The treatment on the barrels causes zero imperfections and is extremely smooth which also enables the barrels to consistently achieve excellent accuracy. Chamber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO (.223 Cal) “5R” polygonal right handed 1x8 twist button rifled barrels. Hogan X-Brake 5 prong muzzle brake and collar nut, which is remarkably effective in recoil reduction but it does not suppress the flash. Made by Hogan Guns. LOWER RECEIVER: Billet machined from 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum alloy with integral oversized trigger guard for use with heavy gloves. Wire E.D.M.’d flared Magwell, ambidextrous bolt release lever machined into the lower receiver. Finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green colors. PISTOL GRIP and STOCKS: ERGO™ pistol grip, VLTOR™ 6-position retractable buttstock with Mil-Spec tube. Non slip special compound rubber butt pad. Reversible for right or left handed shooters. Finished in black, O.D. Green, Tan or Clear anodize, NP3™ or Cerakote™ Dark Earth or O.D. Green colors. TRIGGER: HOGAN “Gold Standard”™ trigger system, 4.5 lb. non-adjustable pull, (for zero failure) single stage competition trigger. Trigger, hammer & disconnector E.D.M.’d from A2 tool steel. Melonite heat treated for long life. Pin tubes are black oxide coated 8620 steel. Housing precision machined from 6061 billet aluminum. Deep gold anodize finish. High temp silicone cord base cushions. Complete with KNS™ precision non-rotating pins. ACCESSORIES: HOGAN rifles come complete with 48" black plastic hard case with foam liner, ERGO™ LowPro rail covers Owner's manual HOGAN vinyl sticker Please Know Your State Laws Before Bidding. Pleas Add 3% fee for credit card payment. This Rifle is NP3 Coated. NP3™ plating: combination of a nickel alloy plating combined with Polytetrafluoethylene (Teflon). NP3™ metal finish offers many benefits. NP3 permits firing for longer periods of time between cleaning, dirt and powder residue have no wet or oily surface to cling to. When cleaning is required, the effort needed is minimal - usually requiring only a soft cloth.

title: For Sale:  Taurus 9mm PT 92 AF
postcontent:
If interested call/ text REDACTED or send email

This pistol is a licensed reproduction of the Beretta 92, and comes in a variety of finishes with a variety of grip styles.
Like the Beretta, the Taurus PT92 utilizes the open-slide design where the upper portion of the slide is cut away exposing much of the barrel itself. The original PT92 was exactly like the original Beretta 92, though it was also unusual for the time in that it featured a squared trigger guard for supporting the index finger of the opposite hand while firing, a feature which was subsequently introduced to the Beretta 92 with the 92SB-F (92F) model in 1985. The Taurus PT92 is less expensive than the Beretta 92 in most cases.
Other versions of the PT92 include the PT99, which has an adjustable rear sight and a taller front sight, the compact PT92C version, and the PT100 and PT101, which are .40 S&W versions of the PT92 and PT99, respectively.
The Taurus PT92 has undergone many revisions in design since it was originally produced in the mid-1980s. Early PT92s and PT99s did not feature the third safety position decocker that is now standard; this feature was added to the second-generation models in the early-1990s, which also included the three-dot sights found on the Beretta 92F. A third revision in the late-90s changed the grip and slide design (which now has wider cocking serrations than PT92s manufactured before 1997).
More recently (as of 2005), Taurus has begun manufacturing the PT92 with built-in accessory rails on the frame, a feature found on the newer Beretta M9A1, a military upgrade of the Beretta 92F from which the PT92 is derived. While 15-round magazines were standard for the PT92 for many years, Taurus now manufactures 17-round magazines for the gun in order to give it comparable firepower to the Glock 17, and aftermarket 30-round magazines are also available.
